.TH mlib_ImageConstMulShift 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_ImageConstMulShift \- multiply with a constant, with shifting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR.\|.\|. ] \fIfile\fR.\|.\|. \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR.\|.\|. ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_ImageConstMulShift\fR(\fBmlib_image *\fIdst\fR, \fBconst mlib_image *\fIsrc\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_s32 *\fIc\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIshift\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_ImageConstMulShift()\fR function multiplies each pixel in an
image by a constant value on a pixel-by-pixel basis. It scales the result by
a right shift and writes the result to the destination image on a
pixel-by-pixel basis.
.sp
.LP
It uses the following equation:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
dst[x][y][i] = c[i] * src[x][y][i] * 2**(-shift)
.fi
.in -2

.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.I dst
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Pointer to destination image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.I src
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Pointer to source image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.I c
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Constant by which each pixel is multiplied.
.B c[i]
contains the
constant for channel
.BR i .
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIshift\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Right shifting factor.
.BR "0 \(<= shift \(<= 31" .
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns
.B MLIB_SUCCESS
if successful. Otherwise it returns
.BR MLIB_FAILURE .
